2. The office of a member of the Board shall be vacated—
(a) if he dies;
(b) if he ceases to be qualified;
(c) if he becomes bankrupt, lunatic or of unsound mind;
(d) if he absents himself from three consecutive meetings without leave of the
Board; or
(e) in the event of his resignation being accepted by the Minister.
